.TH VAULTSIGN 1 "2026-03-25" "VaultSign" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
vaultsign \- OIDC authentication and SSH key signing for HashiCorp Vault and OpenBao
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vaultsign
[\fI\-\-minimize\fR]
[\fI\-\-debug\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B VaultSign
is a GTK4/libadwaita desktop application that authenticates users via OIDC
(OpenID Connect) to a HashiCorp Vault or OpenBao server and signs SSH keys
using the server's SSH client signer backend.
.PP
The signed certificate and private key are automatically added to the local
ssh\-agent, enabling passwordless SSH access to hosts that trust the
Vault/OpenBao CA.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-minimize
Start minimized to the system tray without showing the main window.
Useful for autostart at login.
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable the GTK Inspector and verbose GLib logging for troubleshooting.
.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B OIDC Authentication
Opens a browser for OIDC login, then stores the resulting Vault token.
.TP
.B SSH Key Signing
Signs the configured SSH public key via the Vault SSH client signer backend.
.TP
.B Certificate Monitoring
Displays an animated countdown ring showing remaining certificate validity.
Sends desktop notifications when the certificate is about to expire.
.TP
.B Multiple Profiles
Supports multiple server/role configurations that can be switched,
exported, and imported.
.TP
.B SSH Agent Management
Lists keys loaded in ssh\-agent with the ability to add or remove them.
.TP
.B System Tray
Optional system tray icon (requires AppIndicator3) showing certificate status.
.TP
.B Session History
Logs authentication and renewal events for audit purposes.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored in
.IR ~/.config/vaultsign/config.json .
.PP
Each profile contains:
.TP
.B vault_addr
URL of the Vault/OpenBao server (e.g., https://vault.example.com:8200/).
.TP
.B vault_cli_path
Path to the
.B vault
or
.B bao
CLI binary. Can be just the binary name if it is in PATH.
.TP
.B ssh_key_path
Path to the SSH private key (e.g., ~/.ssh/id_ed25519).
The public key is assumed to be at the same path with a .pub extension.
.TP
.B role
OIDC role name for authentication and key signing.
.TP
.B expiry_warn_minutes
Number of minutes before certificate expiry to send a warning notification
(default: 15).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/vaultsign/config.json
Application configuration and profiles.
.TP
.I ~/.config/vaultsign/history.json
Session history log (authentication and renewal events).
.TP
.I ~/.config/autostart/vaultsign.desktop
Autostart desktop entry (created when "Start at Login" is enabled).
.TP
.I SSH_KEY_PATH\-cert.pub
Signed SSH certificate written by the signing operation.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B VAULT_ADDR
Set automatically from the active profile's server address when invoking
the vault/bao CLI.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vault (1),
.BR bao (1),
.BR ssh\-agent (1),
.BR ssh\-add (1),
.BR ssh\-keygen (1)
